  "extraHighlightWords": [
    {
      "word": "timer",
      "pos": "n.",
      "zh": "計時器",
      "phonetic": "",
      "level": "extra",
      "firstOccurrenceSentenceIndex": 11,
      "highlightType": "extra-high-frequency"
    }
  ],
  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "The office secretary kept every old letter in careful order, by year and by price of postage, she liked to joke.",
      "zh": "辦公室秘書把每一封舊信都按照年份仔細分類，她開玩笑說連郵資的價格都有記錄。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"People don't send much mail anymore,\" she said, \"but the school kept every package and every order form.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「現在很少人寄信了，但學校還是留著每一個包裹和訂購單。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Tan, who still came by to fix the school clock every month, was the first person they asked about the old library.",
      "zh": "每個月還是會來修學校鐘的陳先生，是他們第一個問起舊圖書館的人。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Wires and clocks, that's my job,\" he said. \"But that room has been closed since before I started working here.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「電線跟鐘，那是我的工作，但那個房間在我來這裡工作之前就關了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "He did remember one thing, though: an old sign that used to hang outside the door.",
      "zh": "不過他還記得一件事：門外曾經掛過一塊舊招牌。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"It said something about staying open in the evening,\" he said. \"I never really understood it.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「上面寫著晚上開放之類的話，我一直不太懂那是什麼意思。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "That was enough for Coco to try the school office, where old records were kept on tall gray shelves.",
      "zh": "這對 Coco 來說已經足夠讓她去試試學校辦公室，那裡的舊紀錄都收在高高的灰色架子上。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The office secretary was surprised anyone still remembered the room at all.",
      "zh": "辦公室的秘書很驚訝居然還有人記得那個房間。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That was the Evening Study Hall,\" she said, pulling out a few old papers. \"For students who had jobs after school.\"",
      "zh": "她說：「那是晚間自習室。」一邊抽出幾張舊紙：「給放學後要打工的學生用的。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Years ago, some students could only study after their evening jobs ended, sometimes as late as nine o'clock.",
      "zh": "好幾年前，有些學生只能等傍晚打工結束後才能唸書，有時候要等到晚上九點。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The school kept the old library open late for them, with one small light left on so the room never felt completely dark.",
      "zh": "學校特地讓那間舊圖書館晚一點才關，留一盞小燈，讓房間不至於完全黑暗。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"The timer was installed so the light would turn on by itself,\" the secretary explained. \"In case a teacher forgot, or left early.\"",
      "zh": "秘書解釋：「裝那個計時器，是為了讓燈能自己亮起來，免得老師忘記，或提早離開。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice leaned closer. \"So nine fifteen wasn't random.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 靠近了一點：「所以九點十五分不是隨便選的。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"No,\" the secretary said. \"That was closing time. Fifteen minutes after the last student usually finished.\"",
      "zh": "秘書說：「不是，那就是關門時間，通常在最後一個學生唸完書後十五分鐘。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco asked when the program ended.",
      "zh": "Coco 問這個計畫是什麼時候結束的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"About twelve years ago,\" the secretary said. \"Fewer students needed it. The room became a room for boxes instead.\"",
      "zh": "秘書說：「大概十二年前，需要的學生越來越少，這個房間就變成了放箱子的房間。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"But somebody forgot to remove the timer,\" Coco said slowly.",
      "zh": "Coco 慢慢地說：「但有人忘了把那個計時器拆掉。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The secretary looked through the papers one more time. \"There's a name here, for whoever set the room up in the first place.\"",
      "zh": "秘書又翻了一次那些紙：「這裡有個名字，是最一開始設置這個房間的人。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "She turned the papers around so they could read it: Mr. Yang, Night Worker.",
      "zh": "她把那些紙轉過來給他們看：楊先生，夜間工友。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Is he still around?\" Bernice asked, already reaching for her notebook.",
      "zh": "Bernice 問：「他現在還在嗎？」已經伸手去拿她的筆記本。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The secretary's face changed just slightly. \"Mr. Yang passed away eight years ago,\" she said quietly.",
      "zh": "秘書的表情微微變了：「楊先生八年前就過世了。」她小聲說。"
    },
    {
      "en": "For a moment, neither Coco nor Bernice knew what to say.",
      "zh": "有那麼一刻，Coco 和 Bernice 都不知道該說什麼。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"So the timer has been doing his job,\" Coco said finally, \"for eight years, all by itself, with nobody asking it to.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 最後說：「所以這八年來，這個計時器一直在做他的工作，完全靠自己，沒有人叫它做。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice looked back toward the old library, and for once, she had nothing funny to say.",
      "zh": "Bernice 回頭看向舊圖書館的方向，這一次，她一句好笑的話都說不出來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The secretary said her job was mostly simple actions repeated all day: collect the mail, copy a few pages, and answer the same questions.",
      "zh": "秘書說她的工作大部分是一整天重複的簡單動作：收信、影印幾頁文件，還有回答一樣的問題。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I used to hate this job,\" she admitted, \"but I've learned to enjoy the quiet parts of it.\"",
      "zh": "她坦承：「我以前很討厭這份工作，但後來學會享受它安靜的那一面。」"
    }
  ],
